natural problem: Two more than three times $B$ is equal to 20. What is the value of $B$?
natural solution: From the problem, we can write the following equation: \[3B + 2 = 20.\]Simplifying,  \begin{align} 3B &= 18\\ B &= \boxed{6}. \end{align}
